    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @fvoverscan, sorry for the delayed answer. You can imagine the way how InstantSearch.js works with this: one instance / one request to Algolia. This is not true but you got the idea. That's why you cannot provide distinct at the widget level because each widget is one \"parameter\" of the search.\r\n\r\nWith the given record structure I'm not sure this is something achievable. But why do you have to duplicate the content for both the merchant and the product? You can store all the merchants inside the product. Then you can to declare the `merchants.name` as facet, it should solve the issue.",
